      "emotional_tags": ["feedback_importance", "wisdom", "priority_clarity"],
      "source": "https://brucebolt.us/blogs/news/how-to-increase-golf-swing-speed",
      "speed_mentioned": null,
      "priority": "HIGH"
    },
    {
      "id": "SPD-014",
      "quote": "One of the most common speed blockers is excessive grip pressure. Squeezing the club too tightly restricts wrist hinge and prevents the natural release that creates clubhead speed.",
      "bucket": "FRUSTRATIONS_AND_STRUGGLES",
      "physical_tag": "speed_training",
      "emotional_tags": ["common_mistake", "self_sabotage", "tension"],
      "source": "https://brucebolt.us/blogs/news/how-to-increase-golf-swing-speed",
      "speed_mentioned": null,
      "priority": "HIGH"
    },
    {
      "id": "SPD-015",
      "quote": "Try maintaining a grip pressure of around 4-5 on a scale of 1-10. This 'Goldilocks zone' gives you enough control without restricting your swing speed.",
      "bucket": "LEARNING_AND_IMPROVEMENT",
      "physical_tag": "speed_training",
      "emotional_tags": ["actionable_tip", "balance"],
      "source": "https://brucebolt.us/blogs/news/how-to-increase-golf-swing-speed",
      "speed_mentioned": null,
      "priority": "STANDARD"
    },
    {
      "id": "SPD-016",
      "quote": "Practice these drills for 15 minutes, three times weekly. Be patient - most golfers see significant speed gains within 4-6 weeks.",
      "bucket": "LEARNING_AND_IMPROVEMENT",
      "physical_tag": "speed_training",
      "emotional_tags": ["commitment", "patience", "realistic_timeline"],
      "source": "https://brucebolt.us/blogs/news/how-to-increase-golf-swing-speed",
      "speed_mentioned": null,
      "priority": "STANDARD"
    },
    {
      "id": "SPD-017",
      "quote": "Casting the club, releasing your wrist angles too early in the downswing, is one of the biggest killers of clubhead speed. When you lose leverage, you lose power and control.",
      "bucket": "FRUSTRATIONS_AND_STRUGGLES",
      "physical_tag": "speed_training",
      "emotional_tags": ["common_mistake", "power_loss", "technical_flaw"],
      "source": "https://hackmotion.com/how-to-increase-clubhead-speed/",
      "speed_mentioned": null,
      "priority": "HIGH"
    },
    {
      "id": "SPD-018",
      "quote": "Excessive grip pressure prompts tense muscles, causing them to contract and restricting your ability to hinge your wrists. An increased grip pressure creates a chain reaction as it causes your forearms to tense, and later, your chest joins in.",
      "bucket": "FRUSTRATIONS_AND_STRUGGLES",
      "physical_tag": "speed_training",
      "emotional_tags": ["tension", "chain_reaction", "self_awareness"],
      "source": "https://hackmotion.com/how-to-increase-clubhead-speed/",
      "speed_mentioned": null,
      "priority": "HIGH"
    },
    {
      "id": "SPD-019",
      "quote": "When these body parts are rigid, you lose rotation, power, and wrist hinge on the downswing, causing a weak strike and a loss of distance.",
      "bucket": "FRUSTRATIONS_AND_STRUGGLES",
      "physical_tag": "speed_training",
      "emotional_tags": ["frustration", "power_loss", "cause_effect"],
      "source": "https://hackmotion.com/how-to-increase-clubhead-speed/",
      "speed_mentioned": null,
      "priority": "HIGH"
    },
    {
      "id": "SPD-020",
      "quote": "Many golfers don't reach peak distances until they reach the 5th or 6th hole, which could be due to a lack of time spent warming up.",
      "bucket": "FRUSTRATIONS_AND_STRUGGLES",
      "physical_tag": "speed_training",
      "emotional_tags": ["missed_opportunity", "preparation_gap"],
      "source": "https://hackmotion.com/how-to-increase-clubhead-speed/",
      "speed_mentioned": null,
      "priority": "STANDARD"
    },
    {
      "id": "SPD-021",
      "quote": "Erratic tempo kills consistency. If your swing sequence is off, especially at the top, you lose the ability to generate and release stored power.",
      "bucket": "FRUSTRATIONS_AND_STRUGGLES",
